---
comment: |-
  yt-dlp can execute a command via the --exec option. yt-dlp appends the downloaded filepath as an extra argument.
functions:
  command:
  - code: |-
      yt-dlp 'video url' --exec '/path/to/command #'
    contexts:
      unprivileged:
      sudo:
  shell:
  - comment: |-
      The executed command may receive the downloaded filepath as an extra trailing argument, commenting it out prevents it from breaking the command.
    code: |-
      yt-dlp 'video url' --exec '/bin/sh -ip #'
    contexts:
      unprivileged:
      sudo:
...
